<h3> Nested Columns</h3>

<p>In the below example, there are 2 Top Level Columns... an "8" (Column A) and a "4" (Column B).
  Within Column A we have nested 2 columns.  If your intent is to equally divide up all of the space available in Column A between the 2 nested columns, the sum of the nested
  columns should total to "12"... or 12/12ths of the space available.
</p>

<div class="row-fluid">
  <div class="col-xs-8 shade-box">
    Top Level Col A: .col-xs-8
    <div class="row"> # I"m a full row and think im 12 but i can only get 8
